  "prompt": "Which San Francisco restaurant has the best okonomiyaki?",
  "response": "San Francisco has a vibrant food scene, and while \"best\" is subjective, several restaurants are known for their delicious okonomiyaki. Here are a few highly recommended spots:\n\n1. **Okkon**: Located in the Inner Sunset, Okkon specializes in Hiroshima-style okonomiyaki. They layer ingredients like noodles, cabbage, and pork or seafood, creating a hearty and flavorful dish.\n\n2. **Chome**: This Mission District spot offers a fusion of Japanese comfort food, including okonomiyaki. Their version is crispy, savory, and packed with umami flavors.\n\n3. **Saru**: A cozy izakaya in Noe Valley, Saru serves an excellent Osaka-style okonomiyaki. It\u2019s a must-try if you enjoy a more traditional take on the dish.\n\n4. **Kiraku**: While primarily known for its ramen and izakaya offerings, Kiraku in Berkeley (just across the bay) occasionally features okonomiyaki on their menu, and it\u2019s worth the trip.\n\nKeep in mind that menus and availability can change, so it\u2019s always a good idea to check ahead or call the restaurant before visiting. If you\u2019re an okonomiyaki enthusiast, trying different spots will help you find your personal favorite!",
